    "DisplayDimInstruction": {
      "additionalProperties": false,
      "description": "Per-broadcast instruction telling downstream devices HOW to dim when the host display sleeps. Resolved by the daemon from the `displaySleepDim` settings.json key and embedded in every `display_state` event so that Pixoo / D200H / ESP32 dumb-apply a single consistent snapshot. Absent ⇒ legacy behavior (full-off when displayOn=false).",
      "properties": {
        "enabled": {
          "description": "Master toggle. false ⇒ leave devices at their normal brightness.",
          "type": "boolean"
        },
        "level": {
          "description": "Minimum-brightness percent (1-100). Ignored when mode='off'.\n\nThis is the requested level, not a promise. Consumers clamp it up to their own hardware floor (Pixoo 1, iDotMatrix 5, Timebox 0 because brightness is baked into the frame), so the same `level` legitimately renders differently across panels. Do not \"fix\" that divergence by forcing a shared floor — it would push devices below what their firmware accepts.",
          "type": "number"
        },
        "mode": {
          "description": "'off' ⇒ the panel must read as dark; 'min' ⇒ dim to `level` but stay readable.\n\nConsumers must branch on this rather than inferring intent from the resulting brightness number: a device whose hardware floor is 5 cannot distinguish \"off\" from \"min at level 5\" by value alone. Where a floor makes brightness unable to express dark — the iDotMatrix firmware accepts 5-100, and there is no screen-off command — 'off' means pushing black pixels, not the lowest brightness.",
          "enum": [
            "off",
            "min"
          ],
          "type": "string"
        }
      },
      "required": [
        "enabled",
        "mode",
        "level"
      ],
      "type": "object"
    },
